  <brief_title>Prospective Comparison of Ampicillin / Amoxicillin Versus Ceftriaxone for the Treatment of Salmonella Infections in AIDS Patients</brief_title>
  <official_title>Prospective Comparison of Ampicillin / Amoxicillin Versus Ceftriaxone for the Treatment of Salmonella Infections in AIDS Patients</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>University of Southern California</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>NIH AIDS Clinical Trials Information Service</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To compare the effectiveness of standard treatment with parenteral ampicillin and oral
      amoxicillin compared to initial daily therapy with ceftriaxone followed by 3 times weekly
      suppressive treatment for salmonella infections in AIDS patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
